Comment: Patzer opening.  When I'm playing amateurs I usually go with Qf3 instead, but Pg6 QxP+ gives white a free rook--always a nice way to start the day.

Nc1 might have been better.  Black gets the white pawn at d6 (after trading bishops), and Nc1 also blocks white's b rook--another disadvantage.  Here (Nd4) black makes back one pawn.  It was probably not worth trying to defend the doubled pawns anyway.
